{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":674,"text":"So, let me add to the complexity"},{"time":2680,"text":"of the situation we find ourselves in."},{"time":5270,"text":"At the same time that we're solving\nfor climate change,"},{"time":9620,"text":"we're going to be building cities\nfor three billion people."},{"time":14577,"text":"That's a doubling\nof the urban environment."},{"time":17907,"text":"If we don't get that right,"},{"time":19604,"text":"I'm not sure all the climate solutions\nin the world will save mankind,"},{"time":24807,"text":"because so much depends\non how we shape our cities:"},{"time":28606,"text":"not just environmental impacts,"},{"time":30860,"text":"but our social well-being,"},{"time":32520,"text":"our economic vitality,"},{"time":34826,"text":"our sense of community and connectedness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38154,"text":"Fundamentally, the way we shape cities\nis a manifestation"},{"time":41349,"text":"of the kind of humanity we bring to bear."},{"time":44032,"text":"And so getting it right is, I think,"},{"time":47166,"text":"the order of the day."},{"time":48836,"text":"And to a certain degree, getting it right\ncan help us solve climate change,"},{"time":52488,"text":"because in the end,"},{"time":53664,"text":"it's our behavior that seems\nto be driving the problem."},{"time":57116,"text":"The problem isn't free-floating,"},{"time":59018,"text":"and it isn't just ExxonMobil\nand oil companies."},{"time":62948,"text":"It's us; how we live."},{"time":66341,"text":"How we live."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68044,"text":"There's a villain in this story."},{"time":69633,"text":"It's called sprawl,\nand I'll be upfront about that."},{"time":73170,"text":"But it's not just the kind of sprawl\nyou think of, or many people think of,"},{"time":76979,"text":"as low-density development"},{"time":78633,"text":"out at the periphery\nof the metropolitan area."},{"time":82132,"text":"Actually, I think sprawl can happen\nanywhere, at any density."},{"time":87340,"text":"The key attribute\nis that it isolates people."},{"time":91054,"text":"It segregates people\ninto economic enclaves"},{"time":94968,"text":"and land-use enclaves."},{"time":96584,"text":"It separates them from nature."},{"time":98704,"text":"It doesn't allow the cross-fertilization,"},{"time":101882,"text":"the interaction,"},{"time":103170,"text":"that make cities great places"},{"time":105617,"text":"and that make society thrive."},{"time":108389,"text":"So the antidote to sprawl is really\nwhat we all need to be thinking about,"},{"time":113155,"text":"especially when we're taking on\nthis massive construction project."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118105,"text":"So let me take you through one exercise."},{"time":120614,"text":"We developed the model\nfor the state of California"},{"time":124404,"text":"so they could get on\nwith reducing carbon emissions."},{"time":128046,"text":"We did a whole series of scenarios\nfor how the state could grow,"},{"time":133566,"text":"and this is just one\noverly simplified one."},{"time":136713,"text":"We mixed different development prototypes"},{"time":139533,"text":"and said they're going to carry us\nthrough the year 2050,"},{"time":143368,"text":"10 million new crew\nin our state of California."},{"time":148691,"text":"And one was sprawl."},{"time":149967,"text":"It's just more of the same:\nshopping malls, subdivisions,"},{"time":153523,"text":"office parks."},{"time":154731,"text":"The other one was dominated by,\nnot everybody moving to the city,"},{"time":158545,"text":"but just compact development,"},{"time":160252,"text":"what we used to think of\nas streetcar suburbs,"},{"time":162834,"text":"walkable neighborhoods,"},{"time":164097,"text":"low-rise, but integrated,\nmixed-used environments."},{"time":168969,"text":"And the results are astounding."},{"time":171429,"text":"They're astounding not just\nfor the scale of the difference"},{"time":174616,"text":"of this one shift\nin our city-making habit"},{"time":178875,"text":"but also because each one represents\na special interest group,"},{"time":184233,"text":"a special interest group\nthat used to advocate for their concerns"},{"time":188646,"text":"one at a time."},{"time":189835,"text":"They did not see the, what I call,\n\"co-benefits\" of urban form"},{"time":194958,"text":"that allows them to join with others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197457,"text":"So, land consumption:"},{"time":199069,"text":"environmentalists are really\nconcerned about this,"},{"time":201907,"text":"so are farmers;"},{"time":203696,"text":"there's a whole range of people,"},{"time":205942,"text":"and, of course, neighborhood groups\nthat want open space nearby."},{"time":209861,"text":"The sprawl version of California"},{"time":211971,"text":"almost doubles the urban\nphysical footprint."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216429,"text":"Greenhouse gas: tremendous savings,"},{"time":219128,"text":"because in California, our biggest\ncarbon emission comes from cars,"},{"time":223967,"text":"and cities that don't depend\non cars as much"},{"time":227691,"text":"obviously create huge savings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231601,"text":"Vehicle miles traveled:\nthat's what I was just talking about."},{"time":234701,"text":"Just reducing the average 10,000 miles\nper household per year,"},{"time":239710,"text":"from somewhere\nin the mid-26,000 per household,"},{"time":245064,"text":"has a huge impact\nnot just on air quality and carbon"},{"time":249968,"text":"but also on the household pocketbook."},{"time":252563,"text":"It's very expensive to drive that much,"},{"time":255580,"text":"and as we've seen,"},{"time":256996,"text":"the middle class is struggling to hold on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260313,"text":"Health care: we were talking about\nhow do you fix it once we broke it --"},{"time":264322,"text":"clean the air."},{"time":265505,"text":"Why not just stop polluting?"},{"time":267520,"text":"Why not just use our feet and bikes more?"},{"time":270972,"text":"And that's a function of the kinds\nof cities that we shape."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275314,"text":"Household costs:"},{"time":277243,"text":"2008 was a mark in time,"},{"time":279565,"text":"not of just the financial\nindustry running amok."},{"time":283643,"text":"It was that we were trying to sell\ntoo many of the wrong kind of housing:"},{"time":288326,"text":"large lot, single family, distant,"},{"time":291301,"text":"too expensive for the average\nmiddle-class family to afford"},{"time":295526,"text":"and, quite frankly, not a good fit\nto their lifestyle anymore."},{"time":299152,"text":"But in order to move inventory,"},{"time":301466,"text":"you can discount the financing\nand get it sold."},{"time":304696,"text":"I think that's a lot of what happened."},{"time":306568,"text":"Reducing cost by 10,000 dollars --"},{"time":309258,"text":"remember, in California\nthe median is 50,000 --"},{"time":312119,"text":"this is a big element."},{"time":314024,"text":"That's just cars and utility costs."},{"time":316677,"text":"So the affordable housing advocates,\nwho often sit off in their silos"},{"time":320901,"text":"separate from the environmentalists,\nseparate from the politicians,"},{"time":325389,"text":"everybody fighting with everyone,"},{"time":327391,"text":"now begin to see common cause,"},{"time":329333,"text":"and I think the common cause\nis what really brings about the change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333837,"text":"Los Angeles, as a result of these efforts,"},{"time":336741,"text":"has now decided to transform itself"},{"time":339789,"text":"into a more transit-oriented environment."},{"time":343185,"text":"As a matter of fact, since '08,"},{"time":344943,"text":"they've voted in 400 billion dollars\nof bonds for transit"},{"time":348916,"text":"and zero dollars for new highways."},{"time":351789,"text":"What a transformation:"},{"time":352981,"text":"LA becomes a city of walkers and transit,"},{"time":356336,"text":"not a city of cars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":357539,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":358570,"text":"How does it happen?"},{"time":359794,"text":"You take the least\ndesirable land, the strip,"},{"time":361955,"text":"you add where there's space, transit"},{"time":364026,"text":"and then you infill mixed-use development,"},{"time":368313,"text":"you satisfy new housing demands"},{"time":370520,"text":"and you make the existing neighborhoods"},{"time":372535,"text":"all around it more complex,"},{"time":374024,"text":"more interesting, more walkable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376840,"text":"Here's another kind of sprawl:"},{"time":379787,"text":"China, high-density sprawl,\nwhat you think of as an oxymoron,"},{"time":383319,"text":"but the same problems,\neverything isolated in superblocks,"},{"time":386777,"text":"and of course this amazing smog\nthat was just spoken to."},{"time":390329,"text":"Twelve percent of GDP\nin China now is spent"},{"time":393582,"text":"on the health impacts of that."},{"time":395803,"text":"The history, of course,\nof Chinese cities is robust."},{"time":399092,"text":"It's like any other place."},{"time":400368,"text":"Community was all about small, local shops"},{"time":403404,"text":"and local services and walking,\ninteracting with your neighbors."},{"time":407571,"text":"It may sound utopian, but it's not."},{"time":409719,"text":"It's actually what people really want."},{"time":411710,"text":"The new superblocks --"},{"time":413281,"text":"these are blocks that would have\n5,000 units in them,"},{"time":417225,"text":"and they're gated as well,\nbecause nobody knows anybody else."},{"time":421061,"text":"And of course, there isn't even\na sidewalk, no ground floor shops --"},{"time":424585,"text":"a very sterile environment."},{"time":427018,"text":"I found this one case\nhere in one of the superblocks"},{"time":431658,"text":"where people had illicitly set up\nshops in their garages"},{"time":434908,"text":"so that they could have that kind\nof local service economy."},{"time":438630,"text":"The desire of people\nto get it right is there."},{"time":443411,"text":"We just have to get the planners\non board and the politicians."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447162,"text":"All right. Some technical planning stuff."},{"time":450993,"text":"Chongqing is a city of 30 million people."},{"time":454190,"text":"It's almost as big as California."},{"time":456577,"text":"This is a small growth area."},{"time":458291,"text":"They wanted us to test\nthe alternative to sprawl"},{"time":461927,"text":"in several cities across China."},{"time":465072,"text":"This is for four-and-a-half\nmillion people."},{"time":468378,"text":"What the takeaway from this image is,"},{"time":470333,"text":"every one of those circles\nis a walking radius"},{"time":473006,"text":"around a transit station --"},{"time":475280,"text":"massive investment in metro and BRT,"},{"time":478944,"text":"and a distribution that allows everybody"},{"time":481300,"text":"to work within walking distance of that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":483935,"text":"The red area, this is a blow-up."},{"time":486256,"text":"All of a sudden, our principles\ncalled for green space"},{"time":489437,"text":"preserving the important\necological features."},{"time":493151,"text":"And then those other streets in there\nare auto-free streets."},{"time":497502,"text":"So instead of bulldozing,\nleveling the site"},{"time":501149,"text":"and building right up to the river,"},{"time":503236,"text":"this green edge was something\nthat really wasn't normative in China"},{"time":507484,"text":"until these set of practices"},{"time":510079,"text":"began experimentation there."},{"time":513063,"text":"The urban fabric, small blocks,"},{"time":515042,"text":"maybe 500 families per block."},{"time":517682,"text":"They know each other."},{"time":518975,"text":"The street perimeter has shops"},{"time":521362,"text":"so there's local destinations."},{"time":523308,"text":"And the streets themselves become smaller,"},{"time":525687,"text":"because there are more of them."},{"time":527241,"text":"Very simple,"},{"time":528816,"text":"straightforward urban design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":531395,"text":"Now, here you have something\nI dearly love."},{"time":534629,"text":"Think of the logic."},{"time":536352,"text":"If only a third of the people have cars,"},{"time":538523,"text":"why do we give 100 percent\nof our streets to cars?"},{"time":542928,"text":"What if we gave 70 percent of the streets"},{"time":546131,"text":"to car-free, to everybody else,"},{"time":548330,"text":"so that the transit\ncould move well for them,"},{"time":550599,"text":"so that they could walk,\nso they could bike?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":552948,"text":"Why not have --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":554370,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":555847,"text":"geographic equity"},{"time":558024,"text":"in our circulation system?"},{"time":560698,"text":"And quite frankly,\ncities would function better."},{"time":564480,"text":"No matter what they do,"},{"time":565794,"text":"no matter how many ring roads\nthey build in Beijing,"},{"time":568248,"text":"they just can't overcome\ncomplete gridlock."},{"time":571200,"text":"So this is an auto-free street,\nmixed use along the edge."},{"time":575666,"text":"It has transit running down the middle."},{"time":577549,"text":"I'm happy to make that transit\nautonomous vehicles,"},{"time":580677,"text":"but maybe I'll have a chance\nto talk about that later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583611,"text":"So there are seven principles\nthat have now been adopted"},{"time":587358,"text":"by the highest levels\nin the Chinese government,"},{"time":590082,"text":"and they're moving to implement them."},{"time":591901,"text":"And they're simple,"},{"time":593087,"text":"and they are globally,\nI think, universal principles."},{"time":595724,"text":"One is to preserve\nthe natural environment, the history"},{"time":599401,"text":"and the critical agriculture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602306,"text":"Second is mix."},{"time":603653,"text":"Mixed use is popular,\nbut when I say mixed,"},{"time":606194,"text":"I mean mixed incomes, mixed age groups"},{"time":608657,"text":"as well as mixed-land use."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612190,"text":"Walk."},{"time":613368,"text":"There's no great city\nthat you don't enjoy walking in."},{"time":616412,"text":"You don't go there."},{"time":617754,"text":"The places you go on vacation\nare places you can walk."},{"time":620330,"text":"Why not make it everywhere?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":622561,"text":"Bike is the most efficient\nmeans of transportation we know."},{"time":626506,"text":"China has now adopted policies\nthat put six meters of bike lane"},{"time":630278,"text":"on every street."},{"time":631631,"text":"They're serious about getting back\nto their biking history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635597,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":637077,"text":"Complicated planner-ese here:"},{"time":639404,"text":"connect."},{"time":640757,"text":"It's a street network\nthat allows many routes"},{"time":644293,"text":"instead of singular routes"},{"time":646128,"text":"and provides many kinds of streets\ninstead of just one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650752,"text":"Ride."},{"time":652120,"text":"We have to invest more in transit."},{"time":654454,"text":"There's no silver bullet."},{"time":656253,"text":"Autonomous vehicles are not\ngoing to solve this for us."},{"time":659341,"text":"As a matter of fact, they're going\nto generate more traffic, more VMT,"},{"time":664531,"text":"than the alternative."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665917,"text":"And focus."},{"time":667155,"text":"We have a hierarchy of the city\nbased on transit"},{"time":671335,"text":"rather than the old armature of freeways."},{"time":674522,"text":"It's a big paradigm shift,"},{"time":677245,"text":"but those two things\nhave to get reconnected"},{"time":679936,"text":"in ways that really shape\nthe structure of the city."},{"time":685443,"text":"So I'm very hopeful."},{"time":687700,"text":"In California, the United States, China --\nthese changes are well accepted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692497,"text":"I'm hopeful for two reasons."},{"time":695156,"text":"One is, most people get it."},{"time":697259,"text":"They understand intrinsically"},{"time":699165,"text":"what a great city can and should be."},{"time":701831,"text":"The second is that the kind of analysis\nwe can bring to bear now"},{"time":706696,"text":"allows people to connect the dots,"},{"time":709936,"text":"allows people to shape\npolitical coalitions"},{"time":712929,"text":"that didn't exist in the past."},{"time":714719,"text":"That allows them to bring into being\nthe kinds of communities we all need."}]},{"cues":[{"time":718483,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719696,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":728018,"text":"Chris Anderson: So, OK:\nautonomous driving, self-driving cars."},{"time":731479,"text":"A lot of people here\nare very excited about them."},{"time":735443,"text":"What are your concerns\nor issues about them?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":738426,"text":"Peter Calthorpe: Well, I think\nthere's almost too much hype here."},{"time":741592,"text":"First is, everybody says\nwe're going to get rid of a lot of cars."},{"time":745190,"text":"What they don't say is you're going\nto get a lot more vehicle miles."},{"time":748508,"text":"You're going to get a lot more\ncars moving on streets."},{"time":751079,"text":"There will be more congestion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752972,"text":"CA: Because they're so appealing --"},{"time":755304,"text":"you can drive while reading or sleeping."}]},{"cues":[{"time":757382,"text":"PC: Well, a couple of reasons."},{"time":758903,"text":"One is, if they're privately owned,\npeople will travel greater distances."},{"time":762898,"text":"It'll be a new lease on life to sprawl."},{"time":764863,"text":"If you can work on your way to work,"},{"time":766902,"text":"you can live in more remote locations."},{"time":768993,"text":"It'll revitalize sprawl"},{"time":771559,"text":"in a way that I'm deeply frightened."},{"time":773916,"text":"Taxis:"},{"time":775794,"text":"about 50 percent of the surveys say\nthat people won't share them."},{"time":779566,"text":"If they don't share them,"},{"time":780964,"text":"you can end up with a 90 percent\nincrease in vehicle miles traveled."},{"time":786597,"text":"If you share them,"},{"time":787942,"text":"you're still at around\na 30 percent increase in VMT."}]},{"cues":[{"time":791496,"text":"CA: Sharing them, meaning\nhaving multiple people riding at once"},{"time":794558,"text":"in some sort of intelligent ride-sharing?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":796558,"text":"PC: Yeah, so the Uber share\nwithout a steering wheel."},{"time":799113,"text":"The reality is, the efficiency\nof vehicles -- you can do it"},{"time":802986,"text":"with or without a steering wheel,\nit doesn't matter."},{"time":805501,"text":"They claim they're the only ones\nthat are going to be efficient electric,"},{"time":809018,"text":"but that's not true."},{"time":810196,"text":"But the real bottom line\nis that walking, biking and transit"},{"time":813790,"text":"are the way cities and communities thrive."},{"time":816978,"text":"And putting people\nin their private bubbles,"},{"time":819809,"text":"whether they have a steering wheel or not,"},{"time":822130,"text":"is the wrong direction."},{"time":823725,"text":"And quite frankly,"},{"time":824900,"text":"the image of an AV on its way\nto McDonald's to pick up a pack"},{"time":830603,"text":"without its owner,"},{"time":832311,"text":"just being sent off on these\nkind of random errands"},{"time":836045,"text":"is really frightening to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":837466,"text":"CA: Well, thank you for that,\nand I have to say, the images you showed"},{"time":840848,"text":"of those mixed-use streets\nwere really inspiring, really beautiful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844048,"text":"PC: Thank you.\nCA: Thank you for your work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":846231,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}